column3: How can you not know what you're doing here?
Listen, man... I woke up in a room and I opened a door and now I'm here.
I'm not trying to start a fight...
Well, good. Go back to wherever you came from. We're doing fine here, got it?
No no no no. I knew there was something fishy about you. [REDACTED] doesn't need your help. It took a lot of time for us to get him comfortable here, and you're not just going to waltz in here and...
If you're hiding things from him, he can't be truly happy, can he?
Like you know anything about it. He's in a much better place now than he was years ago. So you better leave.
